cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with domain adaptation for visual recognition, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a framework that factorizes the data into shared and private parts, which involves machine learning techniques such as dimensionality reduction and feature extraction. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on standard benchmarks, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
